snippet: Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. acknowledged that Congress will not grant President Obama fast-track trade promotion authority, which analysts call critical for deals with Asia and Europe.
abstract: Pres Obama’s ambitious trade agenda appears to fall further victim to election-year politics on Capitol Hill when Vice Pres Joseph R Biden Jr, in closed-door retreat with House Democrats, says he understands why they would not grant Obama the crucial authority he needs to conclude large trade deals with Asia and Europe.

byline.original: By MARK LANDLER and JONATHAN WEISMAN

lead_paragraph: Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. acknowledged that Congress will not grant President Obama fast-track trade promotion authority, which analysts call critical for deals with Asia and Europe.

headline.main: Trade Pact With Asia Faces Imposing Hurdle: Midterm Politics
